Was writ:
>I'm powdercoating my cases silver. Looks kewl. Overheating comes from
>too
hot oil. Paint your proper running engine case blue imetalflake if you
like.<

I would only recommend a "naked" magnesium case or one painted flat
black (what I do - not high temp paint either, just plain Rustoleum).

In theory this will be the most efficient at dissipating heat.  I use
the word theory because I do not have the equipment to prove it :)
Granted I will take Bob Hoover's word for it, as he recommends this
practice and has a much better mechanical knowledge base to draw from
than most people.

Just because Mark Stephen's has nice posters with colorful engines on it
does not mean they are the cats meow.


